      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a full kettle</p><p>Slice your <strong>aubergine[s]</strong> in half lengthways, keeping the green stalk[s] on, then score the<strong> </strong>flesh in a criss-cross pattern, taking care not to cut through to the skin</p><p>Add the <strong>aubergine half[ves]</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 15 min</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1633446637774-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1633446637774-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1633446637774-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1633446637774-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1633446637774-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the aubergine is cooking, peel and chop your <strong>red onion[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>into 3 wedges per person</p><p>Cut your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> into 3 wedges per person</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>green lentils</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1633446639102-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1633446639102-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1633446639102-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1633446639102-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1633446639102-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add your<strong> drained green lentils</strong>, <strong>ground cumin</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and<strong> dried oregano</strong> and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add <strong>half</strong> your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> (you’ll use the rest later!) with your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and a grind of <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good stir</p><p>Reduce the heat to medium-low and cook for 5-6 min or until thickened, then remove from the heat – this is your <strong>Turkish-style</strong> <strong>lentil stew</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1633446641851-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1633446641851-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1633446641851-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1633446641851-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1633446641851-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the aubergine has had an initial 15 min, remove the tray[s] from the oven and press the<strong> </strong>flesh down firmly with a fork to release the juices (this will help them cook quicker!)</p><p>Add the<strong> tomato</strong> and <strong>onion wedges</strong> to the tray (cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 trays!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt - </strong> these are your <strong>roasted vegetables</strong></p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for 15 min further or until the aubergine flesh has softened and everything is tender</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1633446646597-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1633446646597-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1633446646597-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1633446646597-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1633446646597-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>dill</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>remaining vegetable stock mix</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> in a large bowl</p><p>Add your <strong>couscous </strong>to the large bowl with the <strong>vegetable stock</strong>, stir it all together, then cover and set aside</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1633446649896-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1633446649896-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1633446649896-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1633446649896-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1633446649896-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the aubergine is tender, scoop the <strong>softened flesh</strong> out of the skins with a fork, discard the skins</p><p>Tip: Carefully hold the stalks (they will be hot!) to scrape the flesh out easily!</p><p>Chop the <strong>aubergine flesh</strong> up all together until finely chopped</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1633446654089-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1633446654089-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1633446654089-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1633446654089-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1633446654089-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped aubergine flesh</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> (not a big garlic fan? Try using less!), <strong>natural yoghurt</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Stir it all together – this is your <strong>aubergine yoghurt</strong></p><p>Fluff the <strong>couscous</strong> with a fork</p><p>Return the<strong> Turkish-style lentil stew</strong> to a medium heat to warm through</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1633446657375-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1633446657375-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1633446657375-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1633446657375-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1633446657375-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>aubergine yoghurt</strong> over the<strong> fluffed couscous</strong>, then top with the <strong>Turkish-style lentil stew</strong> and <strong>roasted vegetables</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>chopped dill</strong> and a grind of<strong> black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
